Q6 : What is Open/Close principle ? 
Ans : Open/Close principle states that your software component is open for extention but closed for modification.
      
	  open for extention - you should be able to add new features or behaviour to your code but dont change the 
	  old code.
      
      for ex : suppose you have an emplyoee which has 2 non-static variable id and name which you have 
	  initialized with constructor now suppose this employee class gets extended by TraneeEmployee class.
      in this TraneeEmployee class you made the constructor like this that through this TraneeEmployee you
      can use Employee constructor(by using super() inside TraneeEmployee constructor) to assign value so 
	  this means it is open for extension.
	  
	  Close for modification - after we add the extra fucntionality  we should not modify the existing 
	  implementation means suppose you have extended Employee class by TraneeEmployee class . so do modification
      you want in TraneeEmployee class dont change any implementation in Employee class or existing class.  	  
	
